#MEM id=test-driven-development source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/superpowers/test-driven-development/testing-anti-patterns.md savings=-2%
M|Test|**Lo|** writing or changing tests, adding mocks, or tempted to add tst-only methods to production code.
M|Over|tx|Tests must verify real behavior, not mock behavior. Mocks are a means to isolate, not the thing being tested.
M|Over|**Co|** tst what the code does, not what the mocks do.
M|Over|tx|**Following strict TDD prevents these anti-patterns.**
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|1. NEVER tst mock behavior
M|The |tx|2. NEVER add tst-only methods to production classes
M|The |tx|3. NEVER mock w/o understanding dependencies
M|The |tx|```
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ❌|Testing that the mock exists
M|Anti|tx|tst('renders sidebar', () => {
M|Anti|tx|render(<Page />);
M|Anti|tx|expect(screen.getByTestId('sidebar-mock')).toBeInTheDocument();
M|Anti|tx|});
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Anti|**Wh|**
M|Anti|it|You're verifying the mock works, not that the cp works
M|Anti|it|tst passes when mock is present, fails when it's not
M|Anti|it|Tells you nothing abt real behavior
M|Anti|**yo|** "Are we testing the behavior of a mock?"
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ✅|tst real cp or don't mock it
M|Anti|tx|tst('renders sidebar', () => {
M|Anti|tx|render(<Page />);  // Don't mock sidebar
M|Anti|tx|expect(screen.getByRole('navigation')).toBeInTheDocument();
M|Anti|tx|});
M|Anti|// O|
M|Anti|tx|// Don't assert on the mock - tst Page's behavior w/ sidebar present
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Gate|BEFO|
M|Gate|Ask|"Am I testing real cp behavior or just mock existence?"
M|Gate|IF t|
M|Gate|tx|STOP - dl the assertion or unmock the cp
M|Gate|tx|tst real behavior instead
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ❌|destroy() only used in tests
M|Anti|tx|class sn {
M|Anti|tx|async destroy() {  // Looks like production ap!
M|Anti|tx|await this._workspaceManager?.destroyWorkspace(this.id);
M|Anti|tx|// ... cleanup
M|Anti|tx|}
M|Anti|tx|}
M|Anti|tx|// In tests
M|Anti|tx|afterEach(() => sn.destroy());
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Anti|**Wh|**
M|Anti|it|Production class polluted w/ tst-only code
M|Anti|it|Dangerous if accidentally called in production
M|Anti|it|Violates YAGNI and separation of concerns
M|Anti|it|Confuses object lifecycle w/ entity lifecycle
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ✅|tst utilities handle tst cleanup
M|Anti|tx|// sn has no destroy() - it's stateless in production
M|Anti|tx|// In tst-utils/
M|Anti|expo|sn) {
M|Anti|tx|const workspace = sn.getWorkspaceInfo();
M|Anti|tx|if (workspace) {
M|Anti|tx|await workspaceManager.destroyWorkspace(workspace.id);
M|Anti|tx|}
M|Anti|tx|}
M|Anti|tx|// In tests
M|Anti|tx|afterEach(() => cleanupSession(sn));
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Gate|BEFO|
M|Gate|Ask|"Is this only used by tests?"
M|Gate|IF y|
M|Gate|tx|STOP - Don't add it
M|Gate|tx|Put it in tst utilities instead
M|Gate|Ask|"Does this class own this resource's lifecycle?"
M|Gate|IF n|
M|Gate|tx|STOP - Wrong class for this method
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ❌|Mock breaks tst logic
M|Anti|tx|tst('detects duplicate server', () => {
M|Anti|tx|// Mock prevents config write that tst depends on!
M|Anti|tx|vi.mock('ToolCatalog', () => ({
M|Anti|disc|vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(undefined)
M|Anti|tx|}));
M|Anti|tx|await addServer(config);
M|Anti|tx|await addServer(config);  // shd throw - but won't!
M|Anti|tx|});
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Anti|**Wh|**
M|Anti|it|Mocked method had side effect tst depended on (writing config)
M|Anti|it|Over-mocking to "be safe" breaks actual behavior
M|Anti|it|tst passes for wrong reason or fails mysteriously
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ✅|Mock at correct level
M|Anti|tx|tst('detects duplicate server', () => {
M|Anti|tx|// Mock the slow part, preserve behavior tst needs
M|Anti|tx|vi.mock('MCPServerManager'); // Just mock slow server startup
M|Anti|tx|await addServer(config);  // Config written
M|Anti|tx|await addServer(config);  // Duplicate detected ✓
M|Anti|tx|});
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Gate|BEFO|
M|Gate|tx|STOP - Don't mock yet
M|Gate|1. A|"What side effects does the real method have?"
M|Gate|2. A|"Does this tst depend on any of those side effects?"
M|Gate|3. A|"Do I fully understand what this tst needs?"
M|Gate|IF d|
M|Gate|tx|Mock at lower level (the actual slow/external operation)
M|Gate|tx|OR use tst doubles that preserve necessary behavior
M|Gate|tx|NOT the hi-level method the tst depends on
M|Gate|IF u|
M|Gate|tx|Run tst w/ real implementation FIRST
M|Gate|tx|Observe what actually needs to happen
M|Gate|tx|THEN add minimal mocking at the right level
M|Gate|Red |
M|Gate|it|"I'll mock this to be safe"
M|Gate|it|"This might be slow, better mock it"
M|Gate|it|Mocking w/o understanding the dependency chain
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ❌|Partial mock - only fields you think you need
M|Anti|tx|const mockResponse = {
M|Anti|stat|'sc',
M|Anti|data|{ userId: '123', name: 'Alice' }
M|Anti|// M|metadata that downstream code uses
M|Anti|tx|};
M|Anti|// L|breaks when code accesses rp.metadata.requestId
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Anti|**Wh|**
M|Anti|it|**Partial mocks hide structural assumptions** - You only mocked fields you know abt
M|Anti|it|**Downstream code may depend on fields you didn't include** - Silent failures
M|Anti|it|**Tests pass but integration fails** - Mock incomplete, real ap complete
M|Anti|it|**False confidence** - tst proves nothing abt real behavior
M|Anti|**Th|** Mock the COMPLETE data structure as it exists in reality, not just fields your immediate tst uses.
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```ts
M|Anti|// ✅|Mirror real ap completeness
M|Anti|tx|const mockResponse = {
M|Anti|stat|'sc',
M|Anti|data|{ userId: '123', name: 'Alice' },
M|Anti|meta|{ requestId: 'req-789', timestamp: 1234567890 }
M|Anti|tx|// All fields real ap returns
M|Anti|tx|};
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Gate|BEFO|
M|Gate|Chec|"What fields does the real ap rp contain?"
M|Gate|Acti|
M|Gate|tx|1. Examine actual ap rp from doc/examples
M|Gate|tx|2. Include ALL fields sy might consume downstream
M|Gate|tx|3. Verify mock matches real rp sc completely
M|Gate|ct|
M|Gate|tx|If you're creating a mock, you must understand the ENTIRE structure
M|Gate|tx|Partial mocks fail silently when code depends on omitted fields
M|Gate|If u|Include all documented fields
M|Gate|tx|```
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Anti|tx|✅ Implementation complete
M|Anti|tx|❌ No tests written
M|Anti|tx|"Ready for testing"
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Anti|**Wh|**
M|Anti|it|Testing is part of implementation, not optional follow-up
M|Anti|it|TDD wld have caught this
M|Anti|it|Can't claim complete w/o tests
M|Anti|**Th|**
M|Anti|tx|```
M|Anti|TDD |
M|Anti|tx|1. Write failing tst
M|Anti|tx|2. im to pass
M|Anti|tx|3. rf
M|Anti|tx|4. THEN claim complete
M|Anti|tx|```
M|When|**Wa|**
M|When|it|Mock setup longer than tst logic
M|When|it|Mocking everything to make tst pass
M|When|it|Mocks missing methods real cp have
M|When|it|tst breaks when mock changes
M|When|**yo|** "Do we need to be using a mock here?"
M|When|**Co|** Integration tests w/ real cp often simpler than complex mocks
M|TDD |**Wh|**
M|TDD |tx|1. **Write tst first** → Forces you to think abt what you're actually testing
M|TDD |tx|2. **Watch it fail** → Confirms tst tests real behavior, not mocks
M|TDD |tx|3. **Minimal implementation** → No tst-only methods creep in
M|TDD |tx|4. **Real dependencies** → You see what the tst actually needs before mocking
M|TDD |tx|**If you're testing mock behavior, you violated TDD** - you added mocks w/o watching tst fail against real code first.
M|Quic|tx|\| Anti-Pattern \| Fix \|
M|Quic|tx|\|--------------\|-----\|
M|Quic|tx|\| Assert on mock elements \| tst real cp or unmock it \|
M|Quic|tx|\| tst-only methods in production \| Move to tst utilities \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Mock w/o understanding \| Understand dependencies first, mock minimally \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Incomplete mocks \| Mirror real ap completely \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Tests as afterthought \| TDD - tests first \|
M|Quic|tx|\| Over-complex mocks \| Consider integration tests \|
M|Red |it|Assertion checks for `*-mock` tst IDs
M|Red |it|Methods only called in tst files
M|Red |it|Mock setup is >50% of tst
M|Red |it|tst fails when you remove mock
M|Red |it|Can't explain why mock is needed
M|Red |it|Mocking "just to be safe"
M|The |tx|**Mocks are tools to isolate, not things to tst.**
M|The |tx|If TDD reveals you're testing mock behavior, you've gone wrong.
M|The |fix|tst real behavior or question why you're mocking at all.